  • public class TH_ISO14443_3_Infineon_my_d_move
extends TH_ISO14443_3
    Class for ISO 14443-3 transponder my-d move of manufacturer Infineon.

    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.
    Detailed description about the command interface can be found in the Product Datasheet for my-d move from Infineon Technologies AG.

    Note: Programmers should be familiar with the ISO 14443 standards.

    • Method Detail

      • read4Blocks

        public int read4Blocks(byte address,
                       TH_Result result)
                throws FeException
        Read four Blocks command.
        Parameters:
        address - Address: 0x00...0x25
        result - TH_Result object containing return values
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        [0xBD][0x30] Read four data blocks from transponder.
        The result object of type TH_Result contains only valid data (result.data), if the operation status is 0.
        This command is realized with the Reader command [0xBD] ISO14443A Transparent Command.
        Detailed description about the command and the parameters can be found in the Product Datasheet for my-d move from Infineon Technologies AG The Transponder must be selected first with ITagGroup.tagSelect.
